<!-- Header -->
<header id="top" class="header">
		<div class="content">
			<div class="text-vertical-center">
					<div class="container">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
								<% unless @research.attachment_url.blank? %>
				        <iframe src="<%="http://localhost:3000"+ @research.attachment_url%>" frameborder="0"></iframe>
				        <% end %>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-5">
								<div class="jumbotron">
										<h4>Featured Innovation of The Week</h4>
										<% for x in @research.categories %>
											<%= inline_svg(x.name.downcase + '.svg',{fill:'white',height:'30px',width:'30px'})%>
										<% end %>
									<% unless @research.nil? %>
										<h2><%= @research.title %></h2>
										<p><i>"<%= @research.abstract %>"</i></p>
										<h3><%= @research.author %></h3>

									<% else %>
										<h3>No Researches Yet!</h3>
									<% end %>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<a href="#about" class="btn btn-dark btn-lg">Find Out More</a>
			</div>
		</div>
</header>

<!-- About -->
<section id="about" class="about">
		<div class="container">
				<div class="row">
						<div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
							<h2>Featured Research</h2>
							<% unless @research.nil? %>
								<p class="lead"><%= @research.title %></p>
								<p><%= @research.abstract %></p>
							<% else %>
								<p class="lead">No Researches Yet!</p>
							<% end %>
						</div>
				</div>
				<!-- /.row -->
		</div>
		<!-- /.container -->
</section>


    <!-- Categories -->
    <!-- The circle icons use Font Awesome's stacked icon classes. For more information, visit http://fontawesome.io/examples/ -->
    <section id="categories" class="services bg-primary">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row text-center">
                <div class=" col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
                    <h2>Categories</h2>
                    <hr class="small">
                    <row>
                    <% @categories.each do |category| %>
                        <div class="category col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-6">
                            <div class="service-item">
															<% temp=category.name%>
                                <%= inline_svg(temp.downcase+'.svg',{class:'svg'})%>
                                <h4>
                                    <strong><%= category.name %></strong>
                                </h4>
                                <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit.</p>
                                <%= link_to 'MORE', category, :class=>"more" %>
                            </div>
                        </div>
	                    <!-- /.row (nested) -->
                    <% end %>
               		</div>
                </div>
                <!-- /.col-lg-10 -->
            </div>
            <!-- /.row -->

        </div>
        <!-- /.container -->
    </section>

    <!-- Portfolio -->
    <section id="portfolio" class="portfolio">
        <div class="container">
		<div class="col-lg-12 text-center" style="margin-top: 0px;">
		<h2>Collaborative Researches, Breakthroughs for the Nation</h2>
		</div>
            <div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                	<div class="project" style="background-image: url(' <%=image_url('portfolio-1.jpg')%>');">
										<div class="content">
										Aisa Mijeno, an engineer and social worker, to invent a lamp that doesn’t need electricity, batteries, or kerosene. It only needs salt and water.Mijeno’s invention, called SALt, or Sustainable Alternative Lighting, is created by dissolving two tablespoons of salt in a glass of water. The lamp is equivalent to seven candles or the brightness of a low-LED bulb, and can last up to eight hours.
										</div>
                	</div>
                </div>

				<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                	<div class="project" style="background-image: url(' <%=image_url('portfolio-6.jpg')%>');">
										<div class="content">
											Salamander Amphibious Tricycle is a Pinoy-made amphibious trike that can tackle land and water. Atoy Llava, the man behind this innovation says that it was his desire to do something realy useful for the benefit of his countrymen that inspired him to create SALAMANDER.
										</div>
                	</div>
                </div>

				<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                	<div class="project" style="background-image: url(' <%=image_url('portfolio-5.jpg')%>');">
										<div class="content">
											Fourteen-year-old Ahmed "Amin" Ibn Djaliv Turabin Hataman along with Gokturk Karabulut (not pictured), his classmate at the Fountain International School won the gold medal among other awards at the 2014 International Young Inventors' Project Olympiad in Tbilisi, Georgia. They explored the possibilities of turning coconut into a biodegradable form of plastic. Once the project is proven, they believe, it will open opportunities for the economy of Basilan, his hometown, where production of coconut is considered the primary industry. 

										</div>
                	</div>
                </div>


				<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top: 20px;">
					<iframe width="450" height="200" src= "<%= "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uc4CD1aEFwE"%>" frameborder="0"></iframe>
                </div>
				

            
            </div>
            <!-- /.row -->
        </div>
        <!-- /.container -->
    </section>

    <!-- Call to Action -->
    <aside class="call-to-action bg-primary">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                    <h3>Gather. Contribute. Collaborate.</h3>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-lg btn-light">Click Me!</a>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-lg btn-dark">Look at Me!</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </aside>
